9 Section 2. Section 61-9-420, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "61-9-420. Child safety restraint systems -- standards -- exemptions. (1) EACH MOTOR VEHICLE
11 PASSENGER WHO IS UNDER 6 YEARS OF AGE AND WEIGHS LESS THAN 60 POUNDS MUST BE TRANSPORTED AND
12 PROPERLY RESTRAINED IN A CHILD SAFETY RESTRAINT SYSTEM. THE CHILD SAFETY RESTRAINT SYSTEM MUST BE
13 APPROPRIATE FOR THE HEIGHT AND WEIGHT OF THE CHILD, AS INDICATED BY MANUFACTURER STANDARDS, AND COMPLY
14 WITH FEDERAL MOTOR VEHICLE SAFETY STANDARDS.Each motor vehicle passenger who is under 6 years of age
15 and weighs less than 60 pounds must be transported and properly restrained in a child safety restraint. The
16 child safety restraint must be appropriate for the height and weight of the child as indicated by manufacturer
17 standards. A motor vehicle passenger who is under 2 years of age must be properly restrained in a rear-facing
18 child safety restraint system that complies with federal motor vehicle safety standards. A motor vehicle
19 passenger who is under 2 years of age must be properly restrained in a rear-facing child safety restraint system
20 that complies with federal motor vehicle safety standards.
21 (2) A motor vehicle passenger who is between 2 years of age and up to 4 years of age must be
22 properly restrained in a rear-facing or forward-facing child safety restraint system with an internal harness that
23 complies with federal motor vehicle safety standards.
24 (3) A motor vehicle passenger who is between 4 years of age and up to 8 years of age must be
25 properly restrained in a forward-facing child safety restraint system with an internal harness or a child booster
26 seat that is secured with a vehicle lap-shoulder seat belt, whichever is applicable, that complies with federal
27 motor vehicle safety standards.
